abstract: Paul Manafort, U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman, on Wednesday won the dismissal of New York state fraud charges, in a defeat for the Manhattan district attorney's efforts to hold him accountable even if pardoned by Trump.
snippet: Paul Manafort, U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman, on Wednesday won the dismissal of New York state fraud charges, in a defeat for the Manhattan district attorney's efforts to hold him accountable even if pardoned by Trump.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Paul Manafort, U.S. President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman, on Wednesday won the dismissal of New York state fraud charges, in a defeat for the Manhattan district attorney's efforts to hold him accountable even if pardoned by Trump.
headline_main: Ex-Trump Aide Manafort's Fraud Case in New York Dismissed
headline_print_headline: Ex-Trump Aide Manafort's Fraud Case in New York Dismissed

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives began debate on Wednesday ahead of a historic vote on two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, who is poised to become the nation's third president to be impeached.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives began debate on Wednesday ahead of a historic vote on two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, who is poised to become the nation's third president to be impeached.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives began debate on Wednesday ahead of a historic vote on two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, who is poised to become the nation's third president to be impeached.
headline_main: U.S. House Opens Session Ahead of Historic Vote on Trump Impeachment
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Opens Session Ahead of Historic Vote on Trump Impeachment

abstract: The Trump administration on Wednesday said it is proposing a rule to allow states to import prescription drugs from Canada, advancing a plan announced in July that the president has said will bring cheaper prescription drugs to Americans.
snippet: The Trump administration on Wednesday said it is proposing a rule to allow states to import prescription drugs from Canada, advancing a plan announced in July that the president has said will bring cheaper prescription drugs to Americans.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration on Wednesday said it is proposing a rule to allow states to import prescription drugs from Canada, advancing a plan announced in July that the president has said will bring cheaper prescription drugs to Americans.
headline_main: Trump Proposes Rule for Importing Drugs From Canada; Industry Says It Won't Cut Costs
headline_print_headline: Trump Proposes Rule for Importing Drugs From Canada; Industry Says It Won't Cut Costs

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
headline_main: Factbox: Abuse of Power, Obstruction-The Charges Against Trump Explained
headline_print_headline: Factbox: Abuse of Power, Obstruction-The Charges Against Trump Explained

abstract: Global stock markets mostly dipped Thursday after the U.S. House of Representatives voted to impeach President Donald Trump and the central banks of Japan and Britain kept their interest rates low.
snippet: Global stock markets mostly dipped Thursday after the U.S. House of Representatives voted to impeach President Donald Trump and the central banks of Japan and Britain kept their interest rates low.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Global stock markets mostly dipped Thursday after the U.S. House of Representatives voted to impeach President Donald Trump and the central banks of Japan and Britain kept their interest rates low.
headline_main: Global Stocks Dip After Trump Impeachment Vote
headline_print_headline: Global Stocks Dip After Trump Impeachment Vote

abstract: German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday criticized a U.S. move to impose sanctions related to a new Russian-German gas pipeline, signaling that she wants discussions with Washington but declining to threaten retaliation.
snippet: German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday criticized a U.S. move to impose sanctions related to a new Russian-German gas pipeline, signaling that she wants discussions with Washington but declining to threaten retaliation.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday criticized a U.S. move to impose sanctions related to a new Russian-German gas pipeline, signaling that she wants discussions with Washington but declining to threaten retaliation.
headline_main: Germany's Merkel Criticizes US Gas Pipeline Sanctions Threat
headline_print_headline: Germany's Merkel Criticizes US Gas Pipeline Sanctions Threat

abstract: Defiant in the face of a historic rebuke, President Donald Trump labeled his impeachment by the House of Representatives on Wednesday “a suicide march” for the Democratic Partyas he delivered a rambling two-hour rally speech that overlapped the vote.
snippet: Defiant in the face of a historic rebuke, President Donald Trump labeled his impeachment by the House of Representatives on Wednesday “a suicide march” for the Democratic Partyas he delivered a rambling two-hour rally speech that overlapped the vo...
lead_paragraph: BATTLE CREEK, Mich. — Defiant in the face of a historic rebuke, President Donald Trump labeled his impeachment by the House of Representatives on Wednesday “a suicide march” for the Democratic Partyas he delivered a rambling two-hour rally speech that overlapped the vote.
headline_main: Defiant Trump Rallies Supporters as House Impeaches Him
headline_print_headline: Defiant Trump Rallies Supporters as House Impeaches Him

abstract: The campaign, formally announced on the day President Trump is expected to be impeached, will most likely be her most expensive and challenging.
snippet: The campaign, formally announced on the day President Trump is expected to be impeached, will most likely be her most expensive and challenging.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine, said on Wednesday that she would seek a fifth term in the Senate, formally entering what is expected to be her most challenging and expensive race on the day President Trump is expected to be impeached.

abstract: The Trump administration, eager to show progress on prescription drug costs, on Wednesday moved forward with its plan to allow Americans to safely and legally get access to lower-priced medicines from abroad.
snippet: The Trump administration, eager to show progress on prescription drug costs, on Wednesday moved forward with its plan to allow Americans to safely and legally get access to lower-priced medicines from abroad.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration, eager to show progress on prescription drug costs, on Wednesday moved forward with its plan to allow Americans to safely and legally get access to lower-priced medicines from abroad.
headline_main: Plan to Import Cheaper Canadian Drugs Advances Under Trump
headline_print_headline: Plan to Import Cheaper Canadian Drugs Advances Under Trump

abstract: The proposal is still a long way from being finalized, and many expensive drugs, like insulin, would be excluded from state plans.
snippet: The proposal is still a long way from being finalized, and many expensive drugs, like insulin, would be excluded from state plans.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration said on Wednesday that it would move forward with plans to allow states to safely import prescription drugs from Canada, for the first time.
